8703  a transmission attempt during retries after a collision: 0 =< r <2^k */

8766 /* Bit definition for Ethernet MAC Remote Wake-UpFrame Filter Register */
8767 #define ETH_MACRWUFFR_D ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF) /* Wake-up frame filter register data */
8768 /* Eight sequential Writes to this address (offset 0x28) will write all Wake-UpFrame Filter Registers.
8769  Eight sequential Reads from this address (offset 0x28) will read all Wake-UpFrame Filter Registers. */
8770 /* Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg0 : Filter 0 Byte Mask
8771  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg1 : Filter 1 Byte Mask
8772  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg2 : Filter 2 Byte Mask
8773  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg3 : Filter 3 Byte Mask
8774  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg4 : RSVD - Filter3 Command - RSVD - Filter2 Command -
8775  RSVD - Filter1 Command - RSVD - Filter0 Command
8776  Wake-UpFrame Filter Re5 : Filter3 Offset - Filter2 Offset - Filter1 Offset - Filter0 Offset

9055 #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC ((uint32_t)0x0001C000) /* Transmit threshold control */
9056  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_64Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 64 Bytes */
9057  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_128Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 128 Bytes */
9058  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_192Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00008000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 192 Bytes */
9059  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_256Bytes ((uint32_t)0x0000C000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 256 Bytes */
9060  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_40Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 40 Bytes */
9061  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_32Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00014000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 32 Bytes */
9062  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_24Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00018000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 24 Bytes */
9063  #define ETH_DMAOMR_TTC_16Bytes ((uint32_t)0x0001C000) /* threshold level of the MTL Transmit FIFO is 16 Bytes */
9064 #define ETH_DMAOMR_ST ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Start/stop transmission command */
9065 #define ETH_DMAOMR_FEF ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Forward error frames */
9066 #define ETH_DMAOMR_FUGF ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* Forward undersized good frames */
9067 #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC ((uint32_t)0x00000018) /* receive threshold control */
9068  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_64Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000000) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 64 Bytes */
9069  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_32Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 32 Bytes */
9070  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_96Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 96 Bytes */
9071  #define ETH_DMAOMR_RTC_128Bytes ((uint32_t)0x00000018) /* threshold level of the MTL Receive FIFO is 128 Bytes */
9072 #define ETH_DMAOMR_OSF ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* operate on second frame */
9073 #define ETH_DMAOMR_SR ((uint32_t)0x00000002) /* Start/stop receive */
9074 
9075 /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Interrupt Enable Register */
9076 #define ETH_DMAIER_NISE ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* Normal interrupt summary enable */
9077 #define ETH_DMAIER_AISE ((uint32_t)0x00008000) /* Abnormal interrupt summary enable */
9078 #define ETH_DMAIER_ERIE ((uint32_t)0x00004000) /* Early receive interrupt enable */
9079 #define ETH_DMAIER_FBEIE ((uint32_t)0x00002000) /* Fatal bus error interrupt enable */
9080 #define ETH_DMAIER_ETIE ((uint32_t)0x00000400) /* Early transmit interrupt enable */
9081 #define ETH_DMAIER_RWTIE ((uint32_t)0x00000200) /* Receive watchdog timeout interrupt enable */
9082 #define ETH_DMAIER_RPSIE ((uint32_t)0x00000100) /* Receive process stopped interrupt enable */
9083 #define ETH_DMAIER_RBUIE ((uint32_t)0x00000080) /* Receive buffer unavailable interrupt enable */
9084 #define ETH_DMAIER_RIE ((uint32_t)0x00000040) /* Receive interrupt enable */
9085 #define ETH_DMAIER_TUIE ((uint32_t)0x00000020) /* Transmit Underflow interrupt enable */
9086 #define ETH_DMAIER_ROIE ((uint32_t)0x00000010) /* Receive Overflow interrupt enable */
9087 #define ETH_DMAIER_TJTIE ((uint32_t)0x00000008) /* Transmit jabber timeout interrupt enable */
9088 #define ETH_DMAIER_TBUIE ((uint32_t)0x00000004) /* Transmit buffer unavailable interrupt enable */
9089 #define ETH_DMAIER_TPSIE ((uint32_t)0x00000002) /* Transmit process stopped interrupt enable */
9090 #define ETH_DMAIER_TIE ((uint32_t)0x00000001) /* Transmit interrupt enable */
9091 
9092 /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Missed Frame and Buffer Overflow Counter Register */
9093 #define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_OFOC ((uint32_t)0x10000000) /* Overflow bit for FIFO overflow counter */
9094 #define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_MFA ((uint32_t)0x0FFE0000) /* Number of frames missed by the application */
9095 #define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_OMFC ((uint32_t)0x00010000) /* Overflow bit for missed frame counter */
9096 #define ETH_DMAMFBOCR_MFC ((uint32_t)0x0000FFFF) /* Number of frames missed by the controller */
9097 
9098 /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Transmit Descriptor Register */
9099 #define ETH_DMACHTDR_HTDAP ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF) /* Host transmit descriptor address pointer */
9100 
9101 /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Receive Descriptor Register */

9106 
9107 /* Bit definition for Ethernet DMA Current Host Receive Buffer Address Register */
9108 #define ETH_DMACHRBAR_HRBAP ((uint32_t)0xFFFFFFFF) /* Host receive buffer address pointer */

9126 #define SET_BIT(REG, BIT) ((REG) |= (BIT))
9127 
9128 #define CLEAR_BIT(REG, BIT) ((REG) &= ~(BIT))
9129 
9130 #define READ_BIT(REG, BIT) ((REG) & (BIT))
9131 
9132 #define CLEAR_REG(REG) ((REG) = (0x0))
9133 
9134 #define WRITE_REG(REG, VAL) ((REG) = (VAL))
9135 
9136 #define READ_REG(REG) ((REG))
9137 
9138 #define MODIFY_REG(REG, CLEARMASK, SETMASK) WRITE_REG((REG), (((READ_REG(REG)) & (~(CLEARMASK))) | (SETMASK)))
